  "prompt": "Why am I peeing a little bit of blood? How dangerous is it?",
  "response": "Seeing blood in your urine (hematuria) can be caused by various conditions, some more serious than others. Potential causes include:\n\n1. Mild causes:\n- Urinary tract infection (UTI)\n- Kidney stones\n- Vigorous exercise\n- Minor injury\n\n2. More serious causes:\n- Bladder or kidney infections\n- Prostate issues\n- Kidney disease\n- Kidney or bladder cancer\n- Blood clotting disorders\n\nRecommendations:\n- If it's a one-time occurrence, monitor symptoms\n- If blood persists or is accompanied by:\n  * Pain while urinating\n  * Fever\n  * Lower back pain\n  * Frequent urination\n  * Weight loss\n\nYou should see a doctor immediately. They can perform tests to determine the underlying cause and appropriate treatment.\n\nWarning signs that require urgent medical attention:\n- Large amounts of blood\n- Continuous bleeding\n- Pain or discomfort\n- Fever or chills\n\nA medical professional can provide a definitive diagnosis and proper treatment based on your specific situation.",
